In a large pot, saute onion, garlic and chili flakes in olive oil for 3-4 minutes or until lightly browned. Add chicken broth and thyme and bring to a simmer. Add collard greens and boil for 10 minutes, season with salt. Add tomatoes, beans. Cook for 2-3 minutes. Add the pasta and cook half the recommended cooking time. Remove the soup from the flame and let it rest for 15 minutes. Serve with chopped parsley and olive oil drizzled over the top.